. Cons., 12, pp. 1-12; Stien, A., Irvine, R.J., Ropstad, E., Halvorsen, O., Langvatn, R., Albon, S.D., The impact of gastrointestinal nematodes on wild reindeer: experimental and cross-sectional studies (2002) J. Anim. Ecol., 71, pp. 937-945; Tompkins, M., Greenman, J.V., Hudson, J., Differential impact of a shared nematode parasite on two gamebird hosts: implications for apparent competition (2001) Parasitology, 122, pp. 7-193; Welch, D.A., Samuel, W.M., Hudson, R.J., Bioenergetic consequences of alopecia induced by Dermacentor albipictus (Acari, Ixodidae) on moose (1990) J. Med. Entomol., 27, pp. 656-660; Welch, A., Samuel, M., Wilke, J., Dermacentor albipictus (Acari, Ixodidae) on captive reindeer and free-ranging woodland caribou (1990) J. Wildl. Dis., 26, pp. 410-411; Wilkinson, P.R., Distribution of Dermacentor ticks in Canada in relation to bioclimatic zones (1967) Can. J. Zool., 45, pp. 517-537; Ytrehus, B., Bretten, T., Bergsjo, B., Isaksen, K., Fatal pneumonia epizootic in muskox (Ovibos moschatus) in a period of extraordinary weather conditions (2008) EcoHealth, 5, pp. 213-223; Yukon Elk Management Planning Team, (2008) Management Plan for Elk (Cervus elaphus) in the Yukon, , Yukon Department of the Environment, Whitehorse, Yukon pp. 1-36","Kutz, S.J.; Department of Ecosystem and Public Health, Faculty of Veterinary Medicine, University of Calgary, 3330 Hospital Dr. NW, Calgary, AB T2N 4N1, Canada; email: skutz@ucalgary.ca",,,,,,,,03044017,,VPARD,19560274,"English","Vet. Parasitol.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-67649458008
